label: Negative

text: The TP was introduced in the 90s to make the IMF's operations more transparent. Gradually, the Fund moved to a model where almost all of its country (mainly Article IV, Use-of-Fund Resources) and policy papers are published.
label: Positive

text: Moreover, and crucially, the policy protects staff independence and candor by limiting the modifications that the Board can make to IMF documents to very narrow categories. This also protects the integrity of the Boardâ€™s deliberations by avoiding negotiations of staff's analysis.
label: Positive

text: The 2024 TP reforms seek to further strengthen the policy to essentially (i) support faster publication of board documents and communications of Boardâ€™s decisions and (ii) strengthen the rules and processes to modify Board documents prior to publication.
label: Positive

text: An overview of the (relatively technical) reforms can be found in this Table 1. There are no fundamental changes to the policy, but the tweaks are important to ensure that the Fund communicates transparently and timely in a more interconnected and shock-prone world. /end
